<br>
Why not?  Check out the rave reviews.<br>
<br>
&quot;Averaging 111 damage with my 31 Shadowknight, and have hit for 183.  It's not worth using at all before 30, however... damage cap too low. <br>
<br>
After 30 it's really lethal, though, and after damage caps are all lifted it'll be hitting for hardcore damage. I've dropped Stonegrabbers in Marus in as little as about 10 seconds. <br>
<br>
For those saying Iceflame is better, I have used both of them: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>there are very few (droppable) weapons as damaging as Tantor's Tusk.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
The only unfavorable aspect of this weapon is it's butt-ugly graphic.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Sure there are weapons with the 40/40 40/45 ratio but don't be fooled.  Though the Tusk is &quot;only&quot; 50 dmg, the fact that it's also 60 dly gives it a HUGE dmg bonus (dmg:49 at lvl 60).  So in reality it's closer to a 75/60 weapon!  Now add in a 36% or even 41% haste item.... So now it becomes a 75/39 or a 75/36 weapon!!!!!  Now mind you I am only 33, but I can't imagin obtaining another weapon as damage at my lvl and at that price than Tantors tusk.<br>
<br>
A closing thought on the weapon from another happy camper...<br>
<br>
&quot;When I first got this weapon, I thought it was too slow to be of any real use. It's slow speed does not give me the type of taunt control I get with my Frostbringer/VAVB combination for sure. However it hits like a train. In long fights I get Taunt. The weapon hits typically for over 200 with high hits in the 350 range. Criticals have been hitting in the 300+ range often with My highest critical being @450. My highest Crip so far with it has been 627. This weapon really shines with the mighty and Riposte disc and high haste. With shissar I am doing so much damage that mobs I could not solo with any other means are easily soloable with the tusk. Not that I advise any Warriors out there to solo past thier 40's but the weapon can definitely be a viable alternative to my dual wield combo. I would take care using it as a secondary tank weapon on a raid as you might get taunt after whacking a real tough mob for a while. <br>
